<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Eternal2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Eternal,</orth> adj. everlasting, endless: <bibl n="shak. ven 951" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 951</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 345" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 345</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 13.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 13, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.18.9" default="NO" valid="yes">18, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.18.9" default="NO" valid="yes">18, 9</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.38.12" default="NO" valid="yes">38, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.64.4" default="NO" valid="yes">64, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.108.9" default="NO" valid="yes">108, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 238" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 238</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.246" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 246</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 5, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.263" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 263</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 124</bibl>.* <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.269" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 155</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 21</bibl> (<emph>this e. blazon</emph> == this account of things e., of eternity). <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.361" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 361</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 1, 66</bibl> (<emph>her life in Rome would be e. in our triumph</emph> == would be for ever recorded as the most glorious trophy of our triumph).<lb />Used to express extreme abhorrence: <cit><quote>would have brooked the e. devil to keep his state in Rome,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 160</bibl></cit>.* <cit><quote>O proud death, what feast is toward in thine e. cell,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.376" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 376</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>some e. villain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 130</bibl></cit>.
<lb />Adverbially: <cit><quote>to be boy e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 65</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>